Literature Summarization: LLMs can analyze vast amounts of scientific literature and condense it into concise summaries. Researchers can use these summaries to quickly learn the evolution of the field, stay updated with the latest advancements, identify relevant papers, and grasp key insights without having to read every paper in full. I would evaluate the progress using review papers as references, together with accuracy checking, concise checking, speed checking to evaulate the performance of the model. Special attention will involve concepts that are called different names in different fields, and the same name but represent different concepts in different fields. 
